  "response": "Choosing just one is tough, but I'd have to say **Chandler Bing** is my favorite.\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **His Humor:** Chandler's sarcastic wit and self-deprecating humor are consistently hilarious and relatable. He uses humor as a defense mechanism, which adds a layer of vulnerability beneath the surface. His one-liners and observations are timeless.\n*   **His Development:** He undergoes significant growth throughout the series. He goes from being commitment-phobic to fully embracing marriage and starting a family. Seeing him mature and overcome his insecurities is rewarding.\n*   **His Loyalty:** Despite his sarcasm, Chandler is deeply loyal to his friends. He's always there for them, offering support and a listening ear (often with a joke thrown in).\n*   **His Relatability:** Out of all the characters, Chandler's struggles with confidence, career aspirations, and relationships often feel the most relatable to a wider audience. He's not perfect, which makes him all the more endearing.\n\nWhile the other characters are fantastic in their own ways, Chandler's comedic timing, character arc, and overall relatability make him my top pick. Could he *be* any more likable?\n",
